<dl id="n54145h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54145h">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54145h"> 145(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Madison Man <small>Green</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54145h"><li>FW 25.04 </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/lexa.htm#n54145h">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/l39a.htm#n54145h">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54145h">MS BL 47476b-468</ms> </li><li>JJA 50:274 <a name="ad8" href="../../ff/fdra/ada.htm#ad8">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/a/ad8.htm#n54145h">Draft: I.1&sect;1.8</a>/2.8</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Outre les montagnes, les points d&apos;eau et les cavernes peuvent &ecirc;tre des samiri. Ceux-ci sont particuli&egrave;rement redoutables&hellip; Les offrandes sont d&eacute;pos&eacute;es &agrave; une certaine distance, et le yatiri (<mark>medicine-man</mark>, magicien) n&apos;ose gu&egrave;re approcher de ces lieux sacr&eacute;s. <br>[Besides mountains, waterholes and caves can be samiri. These are particularly formidable &hellip; The offerings are placed at a certain distance, and the yatiri (medicine-man, magician) hardly dares to approach these sacred places. <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 192</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
